Three people were killed when a matatu rolled several times on its way from Kisii to Bondo on Friday.The accident took place at about 6am when the driver lost control in Kisumu's Ayueyo area in Ahero.Nyanza traffic commander Andrew Naibei said he was transporting family members to a graduation.An unknown number of people were injured.The incident came just hours after five people died on Kenol Sagana highway. A lorry transporting logs from Kakuzi farm collided with two matatus heading to Embu.Read: Five dead, nine injured in kakuzi, Sagana accidentMore to follow